content: Subzone of Bukit Merah Planning Area in Central Region, Singapore **Depot Road** ([Chinese](/wiki/Chinese_language): 德普路; [Jyutping](/wiki/Jyutping): *Dak1 Pou2 Lou6*; [Pe̍h-ōe-jī](/wiki/Pe%CC%8Dh-%C5%8De-j%C4%AB): *Tek-phó͘-lō͘*) is a subzone within the planning area of [Bukit Merah](/wiki/Bukit_Merah), [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore), as defined by the [Urban Redevelopment Authority](/wiki/Urban_Redevelopment_Authority) (URA). Its boundary is made up of the [Ayer Rajah Expressway](/wiki/Ayer_Rajah_Expressway) (AYE) in the north; Alexandra Road in the west; Depot Road in the south; and Henderson Road in the east. "Depot Road" is also the name of a two-way road in the area. The subzone took its name from this road. This [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) location article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it. - v - t - e
title: Depot Road
